{"id":14881044,"mediaExerciseId":"8b1abdc3-2f9c-4562-85f0-3d1c5be07192","exerciseName":"10","chapterName":"7","chapterTitle":"Interest Rates and Bond Valuation","groupId":612312,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":232,"solutions":[{"id":5976738,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"This task asks to determine **why the term structure for interest rate is different from the yield curve.**","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":68,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/01/7ac36fbfbd113522055d3be0935c576f/2921a0ac5dae71e334c9ec5b2083f708/lateximg_large.png","width":994},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/01/7ac36fbfbd113522055d3be0935c576f/2921a0ac5dae71e334c9ec5b2083f708/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Let's start with an explanation of the term structure of interest rates. It tells us the pure discount bond of long and short-term interest rates. These rates do not include the risk of default and tell us the different money values for a different period. The term structure depends on the following three elements: real rate, interest rate risk, and inflation.\n\n**A yield curve is the term structure but is based on the bond yields. It is a structure that tells us how the bond yields depend on maturity.**","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":254,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/01/7ac36fbfbd113522055d3be0935c576f/08e6162474e1b9ee169985c5c9f82fd1/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":128,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/01/7ac36fbfbd113522055d3be0935c576f/08e6162474e1b9ee169985c5c9f82fd1/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"c